solution: We have \[0.\overline{73} = \frac{73}{100} + \frac{73}{10000} + \frac{73}{1000000} + \cdots.\]This infinite geometric series has first term $73/100$ and common ratio $1/100$, so we have \[0.\overline{73} = \frac{73/100}{1-1/100} = \boxed{\frac{73}{99}}.\]
chatgpt_solution: We let $x=0.\overline{73}$ so that $100x=73.\overline{73}$. Subtracting the left-hand side from the right-hand side, we have $100x-x = 73.\overline{73}-0.\overline{73} = 73$. Simplifying the left-hand side gives $99x=73$, and so $x=\boxed{\frac{73}{99}}$. To see a more detailed solution on a different method to solve this question, see Solution 2.
